NAME
     collect-log-files - collects all  available  log  files  and
     creates a ZIP archive

SYNOPSIS
     collect-log-files [--help] [--target target]
     [--outputfilepath pathname]

DESCRIPTION
     The collect-log-files subcommand collects all available  log
     files  for a specified GlassFish Server instance or cluster,
     and compiles the logs into a single ZIP archive.

OPTIONS
     --help
     -?

         Displays the help text for the subcommand.

     --target
         The server instance or cluster for which log levels will
         be listed. Valid values are:

             o    cluster_name- The name of a target cluster.

             o    instance_name- The  name  of  a  target  server
                  instance.

     --outputfilepath

         The name of the directory in which the ZIP archive  will
         be  saved.  The ZIP file is name is constructed from the
         target and timestamp, as follows:

           target_yyyy-mm-dd_hh-min-sec.zip

